  <TEXT>
    <Tag>TXT_KEY_CIVIC_DIVINE_MONARCHY_PEDIA</Tag>
    <English>[TAB]The theory of divine monarchy, or the divine right of kings, holds that monarchs derive their legitimacy from the will of God, and that any limitation of the king's power is therefore against the will of God. This provided a justification for absolute monarchs of Western Europe to overrule other social groups, including the nobility and the church itself.[PARAGRAPH:2]The doctrine was popular among both Protestant and Catholic kings, and similar concepts existed elsewhere. The common thread was simply that they sought to govern without regard to the will of the established and often powerful elite classes.</English>
    <L1 />
